affected the slashes.

25:36.326 --> 25:38.829
Your blade, sir, did not cut.

25:38.829 --> 25:40.706
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:40.706 --> 25:42.291
All right, Joshua,
it's your turn. You ready?

25:42.291 --> 25:43.917
‐ I'm ready.

25:43.917 --> 25:46.253
I hope I have enough edge
left on this knife.

25:46.253 --> 25:53.302
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:54.928 --> 25:56.889
‐ Nice, dude.
Awesome.

25:56.889 --> 25:59.183
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:59.183 --> 26:00.768
‐ All right, Joshua.

26:00.768 --> 26:02.144
The position you have,
your rings here

26:02.144 --> 26:04.938
were not an issue at all
with my fingers.

26:04.938 --> 26:07.900
There are pieces here
missing from the test,

26:07.900 --> 26:10.903
but these edges right here
are sharp enough to dig in.

26:10.903 --> 26:12.821
Your weapon, sir, will cut.

26:12.821 --> 26:14.406
‐ Thank you.

26:14.406 --> 26:15.616
‐ Jesse, it's your turn.
You ready?

26:15.616 --> 26:16.617
‐ You betcha.

26:16.617 --> 26:23.665
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:30.756 --> 26:32.132
‐ All right, Jesse.

26:32.132 --> 26:33.801
Your knuckleduster handle.

26:33.801 --> 26:36.595
I'm able to put
my whole hand in there.

26:36.595 --> 26:38.847
The fact that I have to grip
in between, that prevents it

26:38.847 --> 26:41.600
