so it's locked in nicely.

26:41.600 --> 26:44.311
Even though you do have some
rolling on some spots here,

26:44.311 --> 26:46.063
your edge is sharp.

26:46.063 --> 26:49.149
Overall, sir, your weapon,
it will cut.

26:49.149 --> 26:51.110
‐ Thank you.

26:51.110 --> 26:52.569
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:52.569 --> 26:55.072
‐ Bladesmiths, the judges'
deliberation is complete.

26:55.072 --> 26:57.157
They've made
their final decision.

26:57.157 --> 26:59.618
The bladesmith leaving
The Forge is...

26:59.618 --> 27:03.080
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:03.080 --> 27:04.540
Jared.

27:04.540 --> 27:06.708
Your blade literally
didn't make the cut.

27:06.708 --> 27:08.210
‐ Jared, I liked what you did
with the canister,

27:08.210 --> 27:09.670
and I liked watching you work.

27:09.670 --> 27:11.505
You took the most edge damage
during the strength test,

27:11.505 --> 27:13.465
<i>which affected</i>
<i>the sharpness test.</i>

27:13.465 --> 27:16.093
I know you wish you had
those 18 minutes back now,

27:16.093 --> 27:17.719
but they're gone,

27:17.719 --> 27:19.138
and we're gonna have to let you
go because of those reasons.

27:19.138 --> 27:21.473
‐ Jared, please
surrender your blade.

27:21.473 --> 27:23.183
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:23.183 --> 27:25.185
<i>‐ Going home because my edge</i>

27:25.185 --> 27:26.895
<i>didn't hold up</i>
<i>in the sharpness test.</i>

27:26.895 --> 27:29.231
<i>I know I had 18 minutes left,</i>

27:29.231 --> 27:30.607
but I thought I did
all I could do,

27:30.607 --> 27:32.317
<i>and so I was happy</i>
<i>with what I turned in,</i>

27:32.317 --> 27:34.611
<i>and I'm sticking to my guns</i>
<i>on that one.</i>

27:34.611 --> 27:36.196
<i>I just hope that I</i>
<i>represented my friends</i>

27:36.196 --> 27:38.323
and family to the best
of my abilities.

27:38.323 --> 27:41.743
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:41.743 --> 27:44.204
‐ Joshua, Jesse,
congratulations.

27:44.204 --> 27:45.289
You guys have landed

27:45.289 --> 27:46.623
in the final round
of this competition.

27:46.623 --> 27:48.542
Now we're sending you
back to your home forges

27:48.542 --> 27:51.086
to re‐create an iconic weapon
from history.

27:51.086 --> 27:53.422
That weapon is...

27:53.422 --> 27:55.215
a Lochaber axe.

27:55.215 --> 27:57.885
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:57.885 --> 27:59.928
<i>The Lochaber axe</i>
<i>was the weapon of choice</i>

27:59.928 --> 28:03.390
<i>for the famed Scottish</i>
<i>Highlanders during the 1600s.</i>

28:03.390 --> 28:06.393
<i>Featuring a large 2‐foot blade</i>
<i>affixed to a wooden pole,</i>

28:06.393 --> 28:08.729
<i>this pole arm</i>
<i>was simple in its design</i>

28:08.729 --> 28:11.356
<i>yet lethal on</i>
<i>and off the battlefield.</i>

28:11.356 --> 28:12.858
<i>Containing a pronounced hook</i>

28:12.858 --> 28:14.318
<i>mounted at the tip</i>
<i>of the shaft,</i>

28:14.318 --> 28:16.528
<i>this deadly weapon</i>
<i>could unmount soldiers</i>

28:16.528 --> 28:18.447
<i>from their horses</i>
<i>with a single blow,</i>

28:18.447 --> 28:20.240
<i>then would brutally</i>
<i>finish the enemy</i>

28:20.240 --> 28:21.700
<i>with either the head</i>
<i>of the axe</i>

28:21.700 --> 28:23.744
<i>or with its sharp,</i>
<i>fatal edge.</i>

28:23.744 --> 28:26.496
<i>This medieval weapon</i>
<i>still sees virtual combat</i>

28:26.496 --> 28:29.708
<i>in video games like</i>
<i>"Assassin's Creed Unity."</i>

28:29.708 --> 28:31.793
This must be
a single‐edged blade

28:31.793 --> 28:34.963
that measures
between 15 and 18 inches.

28:34.963 --> 28:38.050
The shaft must be 6 feet
in length.

28:38.050 --> 28:40.761
You must include a hook
on your shaft.

28:40.761 --> 28:45.057
‐ I have not made anything that
is this big or this serious,

28:45.057 --> 28:46.892
so it's gonna be amazing.

28:46.892 --> 28:49.436
‐ Bladesmiths,
we're taking it up a notch.

28:49.436 --> 28:51.229
You will have only four days
at your home forge

28:51.229 --> 28:52.564
to complete this challenge.

28:52.564 --> 28:55.233
After those four days,
you'll return and present

28:55.233 --> 28:57.235
your weapons
to our panel of expert judges,

28:57.235 --> 28:59.237
and after they've thoroughly
tested them,

28:59.237 --> 29:01.990
they'll declare one of you
a "Forged in Fire" champion

29:01.990 --> 29:05.118
and hand you a check
for $10,000.

29:05.118 --> 29:07.871
Good luck.
We'll see you in four days.

29:07.871 --> 29:09.414
‐ Good luck.
‐ Good luck.

29:09.414 --> 29:13.043
<i>[rock music]</i>

29:13.043 --> 29:15.420
<i>‐ We're back at my</i>
<i>home forge in Liverpool,</i>

29:15.420 --> 29:17.839
and I'm ready to get started
on the Lochaber axe.

29:17.839 --> 29:19.341
<i>Finishing something</i>
<i>that's this big</i>

29:19.341 --> 29:21.343
<i>that I've never done before</i>

29:21.343 --> 29:24.137
in such a short amount of time
is a huge challenge.

29:24.137 --> 29:25.389
<i>Forging everything by hand</i>

29:25.389 --> 29:27.432
<i>has its advantages</i>
<i>and disadvantages.</i>

29:27.432 --> 29:28.934
<i>The advantage</i>
<i>is that you learn</i>

29:28.934 --> 29:30.435
<i>how to move steel</i>
<i>pretty quickly,</i>

29:30.435 --> 29:32.896
but the disadvantage
is that it takes its toll

29:32.896 --> 29:34.439
on you physically.

29:34.439 --> 29:37.567
<i>I'll be forged to width today,</i>

29:37.567 --> 29:39.695
and I'll be forged
to length today.

29:39.695 --> 29:41.780
<i>Gonna make the best blade</i>
<i>I can make,</i>

29:41.780 --> 29:44.658
and hopefully
it's a $10,000 axe.

29:44.658 --> 29:47.619
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:47.619 --> 29:50.080
‐ I have four days
instead of the five days,

29:50.080 --> 29:53.333
so that means there's no time
to waste in this contest.

29:53.333 --> 29:56.128
<i>There's five pieces</i>
<i>to this entire build,</i>

29:56.128 --> 30:00.048
so getting everything
to mesh together perfectly,

30:00.048 --> 30:02.759
<i>that's gonna be</i>
<i>the biggest challenge.</i>

30:02.759 --> 30:05.262
<i>I know that when we get</i>
<i>to the testing</i>

30:05.262 --> 30:08.598
<i>that I have to make sure</i>
<i>that this thing is as sturdy</i>

30:08.598 --> 30:10.308
<i>and as stout as possible,</i>
<i>because they are gonna</i>

30:10.308 --> 30:13.478
beat the ever‐loving crap
out of this thing.

30:13.478 --> 30:15.897
<i>This is a war machine,</i>
<i>so I want to make sure</i>

30:15.897 --> 30:18.025
that it is a lightweight blade.

30:18.025 --> 30:19.526
<i>If a blade is too heavy,</i>

30:19.526 --> 30:21.278
I mean, that could be
the difference between,

30:21.278 --> 30:22.821
you know, winning
and losing this competition.

30:22.821 --> 30:26.992
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:26.992 --> 30:29.661
<i>‐ Today I'm going</i>
<i>to profile the blade</i>

30:29.661 --> 30:32.330
<i>and get the bevel on it.</i>

30:32.330 --> 30:34.875
<i>I also want to get that hook</i>
<i>attached today too,</i>

30:34.875 --> 30:37.919
<i>so it's gonna be a busy day.</i>

